snippet: A large increase in commercial aircraft demand boosted factory orders, but businesses cut back sharply on machinery and other goods that signal their confidence to expand.
abstract: Commerce Department says factory orders increased 1.7 percent in September, following 0.1 percent decline in August; large increase in commercial aircraft demand boosted orders, but businesses cut back sharply on machinery and other goods that signal their confidence to expand.
lead_paragraph: A large increase in commercial aircraft demand boosted factory orders, but businesses cut back sharply on machinery and other goods that signal their confidence to expand.

headline.main: Demand for Aircraft Lifts September Factory Orders
headline.print_headline: Demand for Aircraft Lifted September Factory Orders
